I have just forked Linux kernel repository and it&#x27;s size already 1.8Gb according to the "Settings" view.

First of all, I think it&#x27;s wrong. The size of just forked repository should not be bigger than few (dozens?) megabytes. I can easily check this locally when using {{git clone --local ...}}

Second, I&#x27;m wondering what would you do when the repository to fork will be over the stupid 2Gb limit. (By the way, is it still in place for forked known open source projects?)

Reference links in markdown look like this:

{code}
See [the documentation][1] for more info.


[1] https://example.com/documentation

{code}

The bitbucket markdown renderer does not seem to support this.

Pull Request URL in commit messages on a Pipelines build leads to a 404 Error. Further checks, shows that the URL is pointing to "api.bitbucket.org" instead of the URL to the pull request itself.

*Steps to reproduce*

* Open a pipeline build for a commit which is linked to a PR via the commit message
* Click on the Pull Request link from the Pipelines Build UI and you will be redirected to a 404 page.

!2986057817-1.PNG|thumbnail!

When you click the link, you will be redirected to the page displaying as below.

{code}
{"type": "error", "error": {"message": "Resource not found", "detail": "There is no API hosted at this URL.\n\nFor information about our API&#x27;s, please refer to the documentation at: https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/"}}
{code}

Bitbucket Pipelines does not provide a way to save the application log (storage/loga/laravel.log) on test failure.\\
Sometimes with environment bugs during feature testing all you see is a 500 status code ... When you don&#x27;t see these errors on local testing you suspect it is an environment issue, without access to the laravel application log it is very awkward to work out what&#x27;s wrong.

{code}
#!python

Tests\Feature\ActivateApiAccessTest::testActivateValidationAgeidExpiredBeforePlanStartDate
Expected status code 200 but received 500.
Failed asserting that false is true.
/opt/atlassian/pipelines/agent/build/vendor/laravel/framework/src/Illuminate/Foundation/Testing/TestResponse.php:109
/opt/atlassian/pipelines/agent/build/tests/Feature/ActivateApiAccessTest.php:583
{code}

Images like project avatars won&#x27;t load due to an incorrect url:

bitbucket-assetroot.s3.amazonaws.*comc*/photos/...

Note the {{.comc}} instead of {{.com}}

{code}
#!python

- step:
      name: Step 0
      script:
          - echo "Automatic step 0";
- parallel:
      - step:
            name: Step 1
            script:
              - echo "Automatic step 1";
      - step:
            name: Step 2
            trigger: manual
            script:
              - echo "I need to click the button to execute Step 2";
      - step:
            name: Step 3
            script:
              - echo "Automatic step 3";
{code}
